## Coding Standards

### TypeScript
- Use strict TypeScript — no `any` types
- Define interfaces in `types/index.ts` for shared types
- Use inline interfaces for component-only props
- Always type function parameters and return types

### React / Next.js
- Use `"use client"` directive only when needed (interactivity/hooks)
- Server components by default for static/data pages
- Use `next/link` for navigation, `next/image` for images
- Use App Router conventions (`app/` directory, `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`)

### Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes exclusively — no inline styles, no CSS modules
- Follow mobile-first responsive design (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`)
- Use `max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4` for page containers
- Prefer `gap-*` over `margin` for flex/grid spacing

### File Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (`ListingCard.tsx`)
- Pages: lowercase with hyphens as directories (`app/find-care/page.tsx`)
- Types: camelCase interfaces, SCREAMING_SNAKE for enums

